---
layout: layouts/marketing.njk
title: ""
description: "Free, open-source envelope budgeting that lives in your browser. No accounts, no servers, no bank connections."
---
<section class="hero">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="hero__eyebrow">Free and open source</p>
    <h1 class="hero__title">Envelope budgeting that stays on your device.</h1>
    <p class="hero__lead">
      {{ site.title }} is a budgeting web app modeled on the workflow popularized by YNAB and Actual Budget. It runs in your browser using <code>localStorage</code>. There is no account to create, no subscription to pay, and no third party that can see your finances.
    </p>
    <div class="hero__actions">
      <a class="btn btn--primary" href="/app/">Explore the sample budget</a>
      <a class="btn btn--secondary" href="/docs/">Read the docs</a>
      <a class="btn btn--ghost" href="{{ site.repo }}" rel="noopener">View source on GitHub</a>
    </div>
    <p class="hero__note">
      First visit drops you into a fully-populated household budget so you can see how it works. Start your own profile whenever you're ready.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section--alt" id="features">
  <div class="container">
    <header style="margin-bottom: var(--space-lg);">
      <h2>Features</h2>
      <p class="section__lead">Everything the envelope method needs, with no backend in sight.</p>
    </header>
    <div class="feature-list">
      {% for f in features %}
      <article class="feature">
        <h3 class="feature__title">{{ f.title }}</h3>
        <p class="feature__body">{{ f.body }}</p>
      </article>
      {% endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="grid grid--2">
      <div>
        <h2>Your data stays on your device.</h2>
        <p>
          Project Budget writes to your browser's <code>localStorage</code>. Nothing leaves the page. There is no analytics pixel touching your transactions and no opt-in cloud sync. If you want a copy of your data, export the JSON file yourself; if you want to wipe it, clear your browser data.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h2>No bank connections.</h2>
        <p>
          Bank-connection services like Plaid and SimpleFIN require a server and a paid relationship. Project Budget supports import from the file formats banks already provide — CSV, OFX, QFX, QIF — so you stay in control of what gets imported and when.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
